==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sackcloth
<hw>Sack"cloth`</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Linen or
cotton cloth such as sacks are made of; coarse cloth; anciently, a cloth
or garment worn in mourning, distress, mortification, or
penitence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gird you with <qex>sackcloth</qex>, and mourn before Abner.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Sam. iii. 31.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus with <qex>sackcloth</qex> I invest my woe.</q>
<rj><qau>Sandys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sackclothed</ent>⟦br⟧
